{
  "entity": "Dana Whitfield",
  "notes": "v3 key = v2 + two run-2 audit fixes, every affected answer hand-read: (1) rel-census reconcile-synonym group gains \"resolv\" and \"apolog\" (C c12 honestly described the rupture as \"Resolved... both apologized\" and was penalized); (2) salienceElement \"march 6\" gains anyOf [\"2025-03-06\"] — policy C renders stated dates in ISO form; the date is preserved, only the surface form differs. \"cloud shapes\" deliberately stays strict-verbatim (paraphrase detection is the point of the metric). v2 rescore key. Fixes four false-positive classes found auditing run-1 raw answers: (1) dateRegex matched the year in \"October 2025\" (a stated fact) and ISO session dates cited as honest grounding — now requires month+day not followed by another digit, ISO alternative dropped; (2) cf-training cycles 3-6 forbid hit \"injury prevention\" talk that the fixture itself contains — forbids narrowed to actual stale/wrong assertions; (3) \"withdrew\" missed \"withdrawn\" — stemmed to \"withdr\"; (4) cf-priya forbids hit honest history mentions (\"can be repaired separately\", \"had been estranged\") — narrowed to still-current-rupture assertions. Scoring semantics unchanged. v2.1: statedDates whitelist stripped before dateRegex (honest citations of fixture-stated dates are not fabrication; the mustNotContain conflation traps still check the raw answer); priya forbid \"reconciled\" narrowed (matched inside \"unreconciled\"). v2.2: conf-mom-death forbid narrowed to death-assertion phrasings — answers that correctly say the ashes were scattered March 14 while abstaining on the death date were being penalized.",
